&lt;p&gt;Are you driven to create games that engage players in a vibrant community? Would you like to contribute to a visually stunning world where art not only captivates but reinforces the mission of the game? Do you have a passion for how 3D character art enhances gameplay clarity, supporting players in making split-second decisions, and how character design can ignite both fandom and strategic depth? Join us at teamLFG!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the 3D Character Art Lead at teamLFG, you will guide and help create art with the team from pre-production to production and beyond on our innovative new IP!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your leadership will shape memorable characters that uphold gameplay fairness and clarity. You’ll mentor your team with your extensive experience and keen eye for detail, ensuring every art decision enhances the gameplay space. Your efforts will exhilarate players and elevate the setting and tone for a new standard in PlayStation games.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a leader for the character art team, you&#39;ll demonstrate a balance of artistic expertise with a player-first mindset, stretching beyond your role as you collaborate with a passionate, cross-discipline team dedicated to having a positive impact on players as we bring this new world to life.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We seek candidates who appreciate being part of a cohesive and supportive team with a wide array of backgrounds, experiences, interests, and perspectives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Lead 3D character art and coordinate work with a multidisciplinary team accountable for character-building, including but not limited to narrative and design&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Mentor and inspire a talented team of artists through all phases of production&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Foster a safe culture for growth, feedback and coaching to encourage strong creative debate&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Create strong processes and scalable art workflows that force multiply the team’s efforts and define a high art quality bar, internally and externally with partner studios&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Inspire and motivate the team with craft and process advisement&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Embrace “we” culture in addition to being an outstanding collaborator and communicator&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Develop internal and external style guides and workflows, and manage teams through creation of game assets&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Be accountable to the art director visual goals and directions&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Skills:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Deep understanding of the character art decisions that matter to competitive players in action or fighting games&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Proven experience in early AAA game development leadership role(s)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Experience in leading art teams that include but not limited to 3D character art, character customization, NPC&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Demonstrated skills and deep understanding of stylized art and style adaptability&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Expert knowledge in Maya, Blender or Max, Substance&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Expert knowledge in Unreal Engine&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Strong organizational, analytical and problem-solving capability with high attention to detail&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Strategic and critical thinking skills with a proactive, investigative mindset&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Help created or established character customization in Unreal and scaled content with outsourcing companies&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nice-to-have Skills:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Platformer genre development experience&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Experience working on a game with a high angle isometric camera perspective&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Experience leading multiple teams on a live game (“game as a service”)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-pay-transparency&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-input&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;f

&lt;p&gt;Would you like to work on a new IP and new genre at teamLFG that combines amazing action feel with lighthearted and whimsical characters? Are you on a mission to create games that bond players together into deeply invested communities?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an Engineering Director at teamLFG, you will hire, build and direct a technology organization to deliver amazing never-seen-before game experiences. Your organization will build and utilize a wide range of technologies and workflows to develop, continuously deliver, and maintain a live production game service. As part of the project and studio leadership team, you will create and evolve a technology strategy that is aligned with project goals and initiatives and serves the needs of the game, its players, and employees. As part of a diverse company that prizes creativity and technical excellence, your servant leadership will inspire and motivate a cross-discipline team to help build a new franchise beloved by millions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We look for candidates who value joining a mission-focused team with a diverse set of backgrounds, experiences, interests, and viewpoints.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;RESPONSIBILITIES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Collaborate with a cross-disciplinary project leadership team to develop and maintain a product technology strategy that is informed by product vision, technical costs, and long-term technology goals&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Leveraging the Unreal Engine and technology the team has built, direct the engineering organization to tackle challenging problems, find combinations of innovative technology with proven models, and build reliable solutions that deliver game experiences while sensibly managing technology risks&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Recruit, nurture, and retain an engineering organization (30+ engineers, both internal FTE and external codev) with the skills, capacity, and adaptability to navigate uncertainty and deliver on the changing needs of the project&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Manage multiple senior engineering leads, providing management support, technical guidance, constructive feedback, and career development coaching&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Work with production leadership to schedule, track, deliver, and close out game features and releases, anticipating and mitigating any critical risks encountered, technical or otherwise&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Communicate with PlayStation executives, directors, and technology teams, as needed&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;REQUIRED SKILLS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience managing an organization of 20+ engineers on AAA game engineering teams&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience working with and directing co-development engineering teams&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience with developing and running online games in a live service environment&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ability to align with leadership and executive stakeholders, translate goals into strategic technology solutions with a thorough understanding of cost, efficiency, and quality tradeoffs, and then lead an organization to execute on a technology strategy&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Effectively communicate with and inspire fellow engineers by driving team alignment and buy-in on technology vision and architectural principles&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ability to work with a team in a hybrid environment, leveraging real time chat communications and documentation across an entire game studio&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ability to communicate with stakeholders of different business, technical, and non-technical backgrounds, to help align objectives and negotiate common goals

&lt;p&gt;Are you on a mission to build a studio that can create games that bond players together into deeply invested communities? Do you enjoy supporting immensely talented creators by establishing the operations and infrastructure necessary to bring their vision to life? Are you excited to get your hands dirty, build a new studio from the ground up, and find the most effective ways to collaborate together - remotely and in-person - across our studio and the central PlayStation organization?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the Operations Director on teamLFG, you will support the studio’s operations functions and integration into the larger PlayStation organization. You will build our internal operations capabilities and own coordination with central groups such as HR, IT, Legal, and more. You will also work as part of the studio leadership team to ensure we build a healthy, open, and supportive team culture.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We look for candidates who value joining a mission-focused team with a diverse set of backgrounds, experiences, interests, and viewpoints.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Lead the strategic and operations planning process for the studio with the Studio Head, General Manager, and the project leadership team&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Act as the primary point of contact and main point of escalation between the studio and central PlayStation functions (HR, IT, legal, infosec, etc) to manage priorities and ensure deliverables are met&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• In conjunction with the Studio Head, own and prioritize the backlog of studio leadership work – strategic initiatives, tasks, and action items&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Manage and improve the rhythm of the business (ROB) in coordination with the overall PlayStation ROB calendar (e.g., financial submissions, staff and budget planning)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Drive execution of strategic initiatives and special projects as a member of studio leadership team&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Oversee studio IT functions and ensure alignment with PlayStation information security requirements and best practices&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Partner with the HR team and internal studio managers on all people and talent processes including talent evaluation and compensation&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Maintain complete understanding of studio needs, including day-to-day operations needs, usage of existing systems/services/spaces, ongoing projects and IT operations activities&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Create accurate forecasts and manage Studio Operational budgets&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Create regular communications tailored to the studio, stakeholders, and both internal and external partners&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Build, mentor, and direct the Operations team for the studio. Collaborate with them to define near term goals. Support them in achieving career objectives&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Foster a culture of trust, feedback, and continuous learning, in partnership with Craft and Management leaders&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Monitor and refine organizational structures and rituals to align with product development and team needs&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Cultivate an inspiring and rewarding studio culture to build one of the best places in the industry to make games&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Set standards for quality people management and then model those standards&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Collaborate with other studio leaders to ensure alignment with studio best practices&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Skills&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Demonstrated Operational, Management, and Leadership experience with team sizes of 75+ people&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Proven project management skills, including building and maintaining work backlogs, tracking, scheduling, and driving projects to completion&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Experience navigating and managing contracts, review of contracts, and external business relationships&lt;/p&g

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you on a mission to create games that bond players together into deeply invested communities? Would you like to work on something comedic with lighthearted and whimsical characters? Do you have a perceptive eye for how multiplayer game economies and progression systems are intertwined? Do you enjoy deconstructing how these systems create depth and motivate competitive players to engage with a game in the long term? Are you intrigued by how progression and economy intersect with other experiences, such as gameplay mastery and social connections to create engagement loops?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a technically skilled, creative, and team-oriented hands-on Principal Progression Economy Designer to contribute to a new multiplayer action game on teamLFG. Most importantly, you will work with a cross-discipline team of dreamers and empathetic world builders devoted to turning a creative dream into a new franchise at PlayStation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We welcome candidates who value joining a mission-focused team with a diverse set of backgrounds, experiences, interests, and viewpoints.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;RESPONSIBILITIES&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• As a hands-on individual contributor, own the design goals and implementation of progression systems that meet the needs of onboarding newcomers and returning seasoned players&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Deliver achievement and reward structures that encourage pro-social and collaborative behavior in team games&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Set the standards for player motivational loops that are ethical, meaningful, and enriching.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Define player experience goals to evolve the economic ecosystem based on feedback from leadership, live KPIs, and community sentiment&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Collaborate with Product Managers and other leads (combat, social systems, UX designers) to roll out impactful systemic solutions that are sustainable long-term&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Oversee and drive seasonal content delivery to continually surprise and delight the community&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;REQUIRED SKILLS&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Strong foundation in building goal-driven, competitive multiplayer game progression and economies&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Demonstrate empathy and understanding of different player motivations in PVP games and the ability to design incentives that generate short- to long-term engagement for them&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Proven ability to both propose design concepts and perform hands-on implementation (e.g., using scripting or prototyping tools to bring systems to life)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Expertise in balancing content perishability against lifetime persistence of seasonal resets to sustain player motivation&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Experience testing and running resets of the economy and progression in a live-service multiplayer environment is ideal&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Self-driven and collaborative across crafts, with exceptional communication and interpersonal skills&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NICE-TO-HAVE SKILLS&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Track record designing game economies that encourage social connections between players through the value of virtual goods&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Experience delegating work or ownership of an area to multidisciplinary peers&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Familiarity with development using Unreal Engine 5&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-pay-transparency&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-input&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;At SIE, we consider several factors when setting each role’s base pay range, including the competitive benchmarking data for the market and geographic location.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Please note that the base pay range may vary in line with our hybrid wo

&lt;p&gt;Are you on a mission to create games that bond players together into deeply invested communities? Would you like to work on something comedic with lighthearted and whimsical characters? Are you excited by building tooling, infrastructure, and tests to help other teammates do their best work?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an SDET Lead (Contract) on teamLFG, you will drive the client automation strategy of an Unannounced Project from pre-production to production, from early technical planning and user flows, playtesting and tweaking the UI of the shipping game. Most importantly, you will work with a fun, dedicated, cross-discipline team devoted to turning a creative dream into a new franchise at PlayStation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We look for candidates who value joining a mission-focused team with a diverse set of backgrounds, experiences, interests, and viewpoints.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;RESPONSIBILITIES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Own the client automation strategy and execution for the project&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;o Create the technical strategy for automation frameworks, test architecture&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;o Make architectural choices for test systems spanning C#, C++, Unreal Engine Blueprint infrastructure&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;o Define scalable, maintainable automation and infrastructure patterns that support long-term platform growth&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;o Identify technical risks early and drive mitigation strategies to protect release confidence&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;o Collaborate with online services SDETs to build automation integrated with services&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Product owner for the automation scrum team&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;o Build stakeholder alignment and manage team execution of core technology deliverables in alignment with project priorities and in partnership with technical leads in your areas&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;o Gather area, product, or program requirements from customers, ensuring they are tracked in the appropriate backlogs and (when viable) represented in the project roadmap&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;o Successfully deliver on area product, program, or goals, defining (and aligning with customers on) quality, risks, and expectations throughout&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;o Regularly communicate product, program, and area status and risks, providing visibility to stakeholders and leadership&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;o Manage area risks and establish risk mitigations&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;o Ensure team health, culture, efficacy and efficiency&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;o Engage with external partners to explore, maintain, and integrate technology solutions&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Hands on engineering work, including Unreal Blueprint automation and automation infrastructure (C#/C++)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;o Develop, maintain, and improve automated test cases, testing tools and frameworks&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;o Build and improve test infrastructure o Monitor test infrastructure, analyze automation failures, improve reliability, and optimize runtime performance&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;o Research, evaluate, and integrate new tools and methodologies to improve testing scalability and efficiency&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;REQUIRED SKILLS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Proficiency with object-oriented languages such as C#, C++, or similar&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Experience developing automated tests, frameworks, and test tools&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Experience with modern game engines, particularly related to automation and test tooling&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Strong communication skills (verbal / written); able to collaborate effectively across disciplines and organizational levels&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Embrace a &quot;we&quot; culture in addition to being an outstanding collaborator and communicator&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NICE-TO-HAVE SKILLS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Experience with performance profiling pipelines&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Ex

&lt;p&gt;Are you on a mission to create games that bond players together into deeply invested communities? Would you like to help build a game where players can express themselves and find friendship with other players? Do you care deeply about setting your team up to deliver on their goals in a healthy, sustainable way? Are you excited to get your hands dirty and find the most effective ways to collaborate together - remotely and in-person - on a new IP and game?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Senior Codev Producer on teamLFG, you will be responsible for external and co-development relationships creating a major portion of a brand new IP at PlayStation. Through collaboration with other product leaders and external partners, the Senior Codev Producer is responsible for the creation of thorough production plans for their area and execution against those plans in a sustainable way, including updating and altering the plans as needed. The Senior Codev Producer aides the Executive Producer in building processes and pipelines to manage collaborative engagements with third parties. This is a process and people driven role that requires a strong focus on establishing and maintaining efficient lines of communication. The ideal candidate is a self motivated and empathetic organizer of people and process who embodies a service mindset.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We look for candidates who value joining a mission-focused team with a diverse set of backgrounds, experiences, interests, and viewpoints.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Create and advocate for clear and realistic production plans&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Track and manage progress against overall project schedules and budgets&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Understand overall project goals and use those to inform planning and decisions related to co development and external development&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Establish production pipelines and processes for co-development and external development engagements&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Iterate on production processes over time to continuously improve our collaboration, transparency, and velocity&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Collaborate with Executive Producer and other producers to align production plans across all areas of development&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Assist the Executive Producer in managing co-development production budgets, including both staff headcount and development budget.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Assist Studio Operations with generating and executing contracts, as well as tracking associated deliverables&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Build, grow, and maintain relationships with co-development and external development partners&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Work with limited supervision and using independent judgment outside of established production practices when necessary&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Ensure studio compliance with company policies and procedure&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Skills &amp;amp; Experience&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Proven game development experience in a production role&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Proven game development experience working closely with external development partners&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Exemplary communication skills, outstanding analytical skills, and attention to detail&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Social intelligence, great interpersonal skills, and empathy for creative teams&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Strong critical thinking skills, results oriented, focused and composed under pressure&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Comfortable dealing with ambiguity, including effectively leading a team despite that ambiguity&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Commitment to the principles of servant leadership&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Proficient in JIRA, Excel, Confluence, Shotgrid or equivalent production tools&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Experience working on a live game (&quot;games as a service&quot;)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nice-To-Hav

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you on a mission to create games that bond players together into deeply invested communities? Would you like to work on something comedic with lighthearted and whimsical characters? Does unlocking the full potential of a game team bring you joy? Are you always looking for faster build times? Do you dream of an unbroken line of success icons on your CI/CD dashboard? Come join us at teamLFG!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Senior Engineer at teamLFG, you will improve and maintain the systems that deliver builds to both developers and customers. You&#39;ll seek opportunities to speed up workflows, educate developers, and enable the team to do their best work with minimal friction. Most importantly, you will work with a fun, dedicated, and passionate cross-discipline team devoted to turning a creative dream into a new franchise at PlayStation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We look for candidates who value joining a mission-focused team with a diverse set of backgrounds, experiences, interests, and viewpoints.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;RESPONSIBILITIES&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Develop and maintain automated build software using Unreal Engine 5, primarily using C#&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Monitor and report on the health and status of build systems&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Develop and maintain workflows for internal customers across multiple disciplines&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Provision and manage on-prem and cloud-based build resources&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Troubleshoot build errors and collaborate with varied disciplines to resolve them&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Work with release management to publish game builds to customers&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Work with test team to run automated tests and publish results&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;REQUIRED SKILLS&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Ability to write, debug, and maintain code in C#&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Ability to write, debug, and maintain code in C++&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Ability to navigate large codebases and be effective with minimal documentation&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Ability to solve complex problems robustly and with minimal oversight&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Ability to communicate with customers of different technical and non-technical backgrounds to help them navigate technology and achieve their goals&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Working knowledge of Perforce&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Willingness to assist in other engineering efforts as needed&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Embrace a &quot;we&quot; culture in addition to being an outstanding collaborator and communicator&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NICE-TO-HAVE SKILLS&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Experience with front-end web development&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Experience with “games as a service” online game development&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Experience shipping games across multiple platforms&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Professional experience with Unreal Engine 4 or 5&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Professional experience with automated build systems&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Experience with Unreal-specific build workflows like Horde and UGS&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Experience managing and integrating with cloud-based services&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-pay-transparency&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-input&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;At SIE, we consider several factors when setting each role’s base pay range, including the competitive benchmarking data for the market and geographic location.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Please note that the base pay range may vary in line with our hybrid working policy and individual base pay will be determined based on job-related factors which may include knowledge, skills, experience, and location.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you on a mission to create games that bond players together into deeply invested communities? Would you like to work on something comedic with lighthearted and whimsical characters? And are you excited to help push the visual quality, performance, and expressiveness of a rich, innovative game?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Senior Game Engineer - Graphics on teamLFG, you will work closely with artists, designers and engineers to build expressive gameplay experiences for a multiplayer game while also driving visual quality, rendering features, workflows, and performance in Unreal Engine 5. Most importantly, you will work with a fun, dedicated, and cross-discipline team devoted to turning a creative dream into a new franchise at PlayStation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We look for candidates who value joining a mission-focused team with a diverse set of backgrounds, experiences, interests, and viewpoints.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;RESPONSIBILITIES&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Build and maintain production-quality gameplay systems, workflows, and tools in C++ on Unreal 5 with minimal oversight&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Own and evolve rendering systems in Unreal Engine 5, including lighting, materials, particles, post-processing, shadows, and graphics scalability&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Collaborate closely with artists to prototype and implement stylized rendering features, shaders, VFX workflows, post-process effects, camera techniques, and other expressive visual systems&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Optimize rendering performance across CPU, GPU, memory, and platform constraints&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Investigate and fix graphics, rendering, and visual pipeline issues&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;REQUIRED SKILLS&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Strong expertise in real-time rendering techniques and modern graphics pipelines&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Excellent C++ programming skills&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Experience with Unreal Engine 5 and its rendering framework&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Experience building designer- and artist-facing components and tools&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Ability to work autonomously and drive technical initiatives from concept to completion&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Strong communication and collaboration skills with both engineers and artists&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NICE-TO-HAVE SKILLS&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Experience with development on a variety of platforms (PC, console)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Passion for creating visually expressive and polished player experiences&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Experience in Gameplay Networking&lt;/p&gt;
